rrealday%20said%20of%20the%20F-16%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20fighter%20jet%20doesn't%20fly%20quite%20like%20some%20other%20airplanes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20MiG%20pilot%20pushes%20the%20stick%20to%20the%20left%20to%20turn%2C%20they%20have%20to%20bring%20it%20back%20once%20the%20plane%20has%20reached%20the%20desired%20bank%20angle%20because%20inputs%20for%20pitch%2C%20yaw%2C%20and%20roll%20are%20executed%20mechanically%2C%20but%20an%20F-16%20pilot%20doesn't%20have%20to%20do%20that%20because%20the%20inputs%20are%20sent%20to%20the%20control%20surfaces%20on%20the%20wings%20and%20tail%20via%20electrical%20signals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stick%2C%20which%20controls%20aircraft%20movement%2C%20in%20an%20F-16%20is%20also%20a%20pressure%20stick%20on%20the%20right%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20more%20traditional%20stick%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20jet%2C%20which%20is%20the%20case%20in%20MiG-29s%20and%20Su-27s.%20Transitioning%20from%20a%20Soviet%20aircraft%20like%20the%20MiG%20to%20the%20F-16%20can%20lead%20to%20some%20jerky%20flying%20early%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pilot%20climbs%20into%20an%20F-16%20Fighting%20Falcon%20before%20flying%20a%20combat%20mission%20over%20Iraq%2C%20May%202%2C%202008.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65392beb96f7540cd0652d08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22996%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20pilot%20climbs%20into%20an%20F-16%20Fighting%20Falcon%20before%20flying%20a%20combat%20mission%20over%20Iraq%2C%20May%202%2C%202008.%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Julianne%20Showalter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%20when%20you%20had%20pilots%20that%20were%20transitioning%20from%20another%20platform%2C%20they%20started%20rolling%20left%2C%20and%20then%20you'd%20get%20a%20kick%20to%20the%20right%2C%20and%20you're%20like%20'Whoa%2C%20whoa%2C%20what%20are%20you%20doing%3F'%20And%20it's%20just%20that%20muscle%20memory%20that%20they%20have%20that%20every%20time%20they%20put%20in%20an%20input%2C%20they%20have%20to%20take%20it%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Torrealday%2C%20who%20taught%20pilots%20from%20Poland%20and%20Romania%20that%20flew%20MiGs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20time%20to%20get%20that%20out%20of%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20something%20inherent%20to%20the%20F-16%20that%20they%20may%20have%20never%20experienced%20on%20anything%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Hands%20on%20throttle-and-stick%20control'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20at%20least%20some%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20who%20are%20learning%20to%20operate%20the%20F-16%2C%20either%20in%20Denmark%20or%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20command%20and%20control%2C%20ergonomics%2C%20avionics%2C%20and%20various%20weapons%20and%20sensor%20controls%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20at%20least%20somewhat%20different%20from%20what%20they're%20accustomed%20to%20in%20Soviet%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20F-16%2C%20%26quot%3Bmost%20of%20your%20controls%20are%20either%20on%20the%20throttle%20on%20your%20left%20hand%20or%20on%20the%20control%20stick%20on%20your%20right%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Torrealday%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you%20rarely%2C%20once%20you're%20employing%20tactically%2C%20have%20to%20take%20your%20hands%20off%20the%20throttle%20or%20the%20stick.%20That's%20called%20hands%20on%20throttle-and-stick%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20controls%20a%20pilot%20needs%20are%20not%20on%20the%20stick%20or%20throttle%2C%20the%20latter%20controlling%20the%20jet's%20engine%2C%20they%20are%20close%20by.%20The%20MiG-29%2C%20at%20least%20in%20most%20variations%20of%20the%20plane%2C%20is%20not%20set%20up%20in%20the%20same%20way%2C%20requiring%20the%20pilot%20to%20be%20more%20heads%20down%20when%20flying%20and%20limiting%20awareness%20in%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cockpit%20of%20a%20MiG-29%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%20Gallery%20at%20the%20National%20Museum%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Air%20Force%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65395ad696f7540cd0659ef3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECockpit%20of%20a%20MiG-29%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%20Gallery%20at%20the%20National%20Museum%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Air%20Force%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20aircraft%20without%20these%20kinds%20of%20control%20systems%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20would%20have%20to%20let%20go%20of%20either%20the%20throttle%20or%20the%20control%20stick%20and%20flip%20switches%20up%20in%20front%20of%20you%20to%20change%20sensors%2C%20weapons%20and%20that%20sort%20of%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20Torrealday%20said.%20But%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20you%20get%20to%20the%20F-16%2C%20that's%20no%20longer%20required.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Information%20overload'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-16%2C%20originally%20made%20by%20General%20Dynamics%20and%20later%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20also%20features%20a%20variety%20of%20information%20displays%20inside%20the%20cockpit%20that%20are%20designed%20to%20give%20a%20pilot%20more%20situational%20awareness%20and%20autonomy%20than%20some%20Soviet-era%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20what%20are%20called%20multifunction%20displays%2C%20which%20are%20small%20screens%2C%20color%20screens%20in%20front%20of%20you%2C%20above%20your%20legs%2C%20and%20you%20are%20getting%20a%20lot%20of%20information%2C%20much%20like%20you%20would%20say%20in%20video%20games%2C%26quot%3B%20Torrealday%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20getting%20color-coded%20information%20on%20targets%2C%20on%20navigation%20points%2C%20on%20threats%2C%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20an%20information%20overload%20when%20you're%20starting%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Torrealday%20said%2C%20acknowledging%20though%20that%20it%20is%20unclear%20to%20exactly%20what%20level%20the%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20has%20experienced%20this%20kind%20of%20technology%20in%20its%20aircraft%2C%20some%20of%20which%20may%20be%20upgraded%20versions%20of%20the%20original%20platforms%20that%20started%20with%20analog%20instruments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221731%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20F-16%20Fighting%20Falcon%20aircraft%20sits%20parked%20on%20flight%20line%20at%20MacDill%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Sept.%208%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65392c8f356802a56be35f71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22889%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20F-16%20Fighting%20Falcon%20aircraft%20sits%20parked%20on%20flight%20line%20at%20MacDill%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20Sept.%208%2C%202021.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%20by%20Airman%201st%20Class%20Lauren%20Cobin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESimulator%20training%20will%20help%20ease%20the%20transition%20with%20these%20potential%20differences%2C%20but%20getting%20up%20to%20speed%20in%20an%20actual%20plane%20still%20takes%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraining%20a%20new%20F-16%20pilot%20requires%20about%20eight%20months%2C%20while%20a%20more%20experienced%20pilot%20who%20has%20flown%20tactically%20may%20be%20able%20to%20master%20the%20jet%20in%20five%20months%20or%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraining%20has%20been%20ongoing%20at%20the%20Danish%20military%20air%20base%20in%20Skrydstrup%20and%20in%20the%20US%20at%20Lackland%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20Texas%20and%20Morris%20Air%20National%20Guard%20Base%20in%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20long%20sought%20the%20F-16%2C%20a%20proven%20combat%20platform%20readily%20available%20in%20various%20NATO%20arsenals%2C%20but%20the%20jet's%20utility%20has%20been%20heavily%20discussed%20and%20debated%20by%20veterans%20and%20experts%20weighing%2