rry%2520spoon%2520was%2520invented%2Cin%25201995%252C%2522%2520McDonald%2527s%2520explains.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFood%20%26amp%3B%20Wine%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20spoons%20that%20are%20now%20being%20phased%20out%20were%20first%20introduced%20back%20in%201995.%20The%20spoons%20have%20been%20an%20object%20of%20intrigue%20for%20years%2C%20with%20diners%20wondering%20why%20they're%20hollow%20and%20what%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20hook%20on%20the%20top%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20McDonald's%20has%20previously%20set%20the%20record%20straight%20on%20the%20unusual%20design%20of%20the%20spoons%3A%20They%20double%20as%20spindles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20a%20McFlurry%2C%20McDonald's%20staff%20pour%20soft-serve%20ice%20cream%20into%20a%20cup%20and%20then%20sprinkle%20topping%20onto%20it.%20They%20then%20insert%20the%20hollow%20plastic%20spoon%2C%20which%20is%20attached%20to%20a%20McFlurry%20machine%20and%20used%20to%20mix%20toppings%20into%20the%20ice-cream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20chain's%20US%20restaurants%20are%20now%20transitioning%20to%20reusable%20spindles%20that%20are%20swapped%20out%20and%20cleaned%20after%20each%20McFlurry%20is%20made.%20The%20desserts%20will%20then%20be%20served%20with%20a%20smaller%20black%20spoon%2C%20the%20same%20one%20that%20McDonald's%20already%20gives%20out%20with%20its%20sundaes%2C%20which%20it%20says%20%26quot%3Buses%20less%20plastic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20small%20change%20will%20help%20reduce%20single-use%20plastic%20waste%20in%20restaurants%2C%26quot%3B%20McDonald's%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.mcdonalds.com%2Fcorpmcd%2Four-stories%2Farticle%2Fmcflurry-spindles-intheus-aregetting-more-sustainable-makeover.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcdonalds.com%2Fgb%2Fen-gb%2Fnewsroom%2Farticle%2Fnew-paper-based-cutlery.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20October%20that%20it%20was%20switching%20to%20compostable%2C%20paper-based%20McFlurry%20spoons%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FMcDonaldsEmployees%2Fcomments%2F16ycj7l%2Fid_like_to_point_out_this_mcbullshit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20a%20photo%20shared%20on%20a%20Reddit%20forum%20for%20McDonald's%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20new%20spoon%20given%20to%20customers%20buying%20a%20McFlurry%20will%20be%20individually%20wrapped.%20The%20photo%20also%20appears%20to%20show%20that%20the%20new%20reusable%20spindles%20are%20pink%2C%20with%20employees%20instructed%20to%20use%20the%20spindles%20for%20four%20hours%20before%20swapping%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.mcdonalds.com%2Fcorpmcd%2Four-purpose-and-impact%2Four-planet%2Fpackaging-toys-and-waste.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOther%20steps%3C%2Fa%3E%20McDonald's%20has%20been%20taking%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20plastic%20use%20include%20using%20paper-based%20straws%2C%20McFlurry%20cups%20without%20plastic%20lids%2C%20and%20introducing%20salad%20boxes%20and%20cutlery%20made%20from%20renewable%20fiber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20US%20menu%20features%20two%20core%20McFlurry%20flavors%3A%20Oreo%20and%20M%26amp%3BM.%20It%20also%20sells%20a%20range%20of%20time-limited%20flavors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20has%20contacted%20McDonald's%20for%20comment%20on%20whether%20this%20affects%20both%20corporate%20and%20franchise%20restaurants%2C%20whether%20the%20changes%20will%20be%20introduced%20outside%20the%20US.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-removes-mcflurry-spoon-ice-cream-machine-dessert-spindle-mix-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698317528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a4180356802a56be46a11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originI