2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-dead-instagram-tiktok-bereal-replaced-group-chats-messaging-2023-8%5C%22%3ESocial%20media%20is%20dead%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Being%20online%20today%20is%20doom-coded%2C%20it's%20gloom-pilled%2C%20it's%20a%20wasteland%20of%20algorithmically%20attuned%20sludgery.%20You%20may%20encounter%20sparks%20of%20viral%20fun%20%E2%80%94%20you'll%20find%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fskibidi-toilet-is-good-actually-2023-10%5C%22%3ESkibidi%20toilet%3C%2Fa%3E%20erasure%20here%20%E2%80%94%20but%20very%20little%20joy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20always%20so.%20The%20web%20used%20to%20be%20so%20much%20weirder.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20grew%20up%20at%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20that%20era%20of%20the%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20Agarwal%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20just%20a%20lot%20of%20independent%20creators%20making%20cool%20stuff%20and%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20they%20were%20doing%20it%20for%20the%20fun%20of%20it%2C%20not%20to%20grow%20a%20business%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%20And%20then%20I%20kind%20of%20watched%20that%20all%20slowly%20die.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20within%20the%20corridors%20of%20Internet%20Artifacts%2C%20and%20through%20the%20work%20of%20Agarwal%20and%20a%20host%20of%20other%20creators%20dedicated%20to%20the%20web%20as%20a%20medium%2C%20you%20can%20see%20an%20urgent%20attempt%20at%20resurrection%2C%20echoes%20of%20an%20internet%20that%20was%20messy%20and%20unpredictable%20%E2%80%94%20and%20all%20the%20better%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20did%20we%20wind%20up%20with%20today's%20anemic%20internet%3F%20The%20pocket%20version%20goes%20something%20like%20this%3A%20A%20couple%20of%20decades%20ago%2C%20give%20or%20take%2C%20easy-to-use%20web-design%20software%20like%20Adobe%20Flash%2C%20combined%20with%20mainstream%20internet%20availability%2C%20catalyzed%20a%20golden%20era%20of%20online%20experimentation.%20Animated%20series%20like%20Homestar%20Runner%2C%20nihilistic%20absurdities%20like%20QWOP%2C%20and%20single-serving%20meme%20shrines%20like%20YTMND%20dotted%20the%20landscape.%20They%20spread%20not%20by%20algorithmic%20ranking%20but%20by%20word%20of%20mouth.%20They%20had%20little%20in%20common%20beyond%20an%20antic%20sense%20of%20discovery%20and%20childlike%20play.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20web%20itself%20was%20just%20a%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20few%20short%20years%2C%20two%20concurrent%20tectonic%20shifts%20would%20reshape%20the%20internet.%20The%20first%20is%20that%20Apple%20killed%20Flash%3B%20Steve%20Jobs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20170615060422%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fhotnews%2Fthoughts-on-flash%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexiled%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20from%20the%20iPhone%20for%20being%20a%20buggy%2C%20sluggish%2C%20proprietary%20security%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20he%20wasn't%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20which%20made%20the%20once-ubiquitous%20software%20a%20liability%20to%20work%20with.%20Suddenly%20building%20things%20on%20the%20web%20wasn't%20quite%20so%20simple%2C%20and%20eventually%20a%20lot%20of%20cherished%20sites%20no%20longer%20worked.%20Tools%20like%20HTML5%20came%20along%20to%20take%20Flash's%20place%2C%20but%20by%20then%20it%20was%20too%20late.%20Developers%20increasingly%20built%20for%20the%20iPhone%2C%20prioritizing%20apps%20over%20browsers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20transformation%20is%20that%20websites%20themselves%20became%20largely%20obsolete%2C%20displaced%20by%20platforms.%20First%20came%20the%20likes%20of%20MySpace%2C%20Facebook%2C%20Twitter%2C%20Tumblr%2C%20and%20Reddit%3B%20then%20came%20the%20image-%20and%20video-focused%20wave%20of%20Instagram%2C%20Snap%2C%20and%20TikTok.%20To%20their%20credit%2C%20those%20tech%20giants%20did%20democratize%20the%20act%20of%20posting.%20You%20didn't%20need%20to%20be%20a%20software%20engineer%20to%20put%20a%20photo%20on%20your%20timeline.%20With%20powerful%20mobile%20editing%20tools%2C%20the%20act%20of%20%3Cem%3Eputting%20stuff%20online%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20now%20easier%20than%20ever.%20But%20the%20result%20is%20a%20little%20like%20giving%20a%20room%20full%20of%20artists%20the%20same%20size%20canvas%20and%20identical%20matte%20paints.%20There%20are%20only%20so%20many%20variations%20one%20can%20bring%20to%20the%20theme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20in%20lieu%20of%20the%20unique%20URL%2C%20you%20have%20the%20unique%20handle%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamie%20Cohen%2C%20a%20digital%20culture%20writer%20and%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20CUNY-Queens%2C%20said.%20People%20once%20created%20their%20own%20distinct%20worlds%3B%20now%20they%20mostly%20shout%20at%20each%20other%20in%20the%20same%20rooms.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20same.%20It's%20a%20flattening%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeal%20Agarwal%20rejects%20that%20looming%20sameness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20just%20a%20kid%2C%20the%20internet%20felt%20like%20a%20Wild%20West%2C%20at%20least%20more%20than%20it%20is%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Agarwal%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20always%20go%20down%20these%20long%20rabbit%20holes.%20Almost%20all%20the%20sites%20I%20visited%20were%20by%20solo%20creators%20or%20small%20teams%20of%20people.%20It%20felt%20like%20much%20more%20of%20an%20independent%20web.%20As%20I%20watched%20all%20that%20go%20away%2C%20I%20kept%20feeling%20that%20this%20probably%20isn't%20how%20it%20should%20be.%20There%20should%20be%20more%20people%20creating%20fun%20stuff%20on%20the%20web.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20he%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20some%20origin%20stories%2C%20there's%20no%20single%20spark%20that%20ignited%20Agarwal.%20The%20first%20website%20he%20built%2C%20Kidcrash%2C%20was%20itself%20an%20act%20of%20curation%2C%20putting%20all%20his%20favorite%20Flash-based%20games%20in%20one%20place.%20He%20made%20it%20in%202006.%20He%20was%209.%20Like%20a%20lot%20of%20precocious%20young%20coders%20at%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Fairfax%2C%20Virginia%2C%20native%20soon%20found%20his%20way%20to%20Scratch%2C%20a%20programming%20website%20for%20kids%2C%20where%20he%20went%20by%20the%20handle%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscratch.mit.edu%2Fusers%2Fawesomestickdude%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eawesomestickdude%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20first%20game%20was%20a%20knockoff%20of%20the%20reality-TV%20competition%20show%20%26quot%3BWipeout.%26quot%3B%20Then%2012%2C%20he%20offered%20to%20build%20a%20new%20game%20level%20for%20every%2015%20%26quot%3Blove-its%26quot%3B%20he%20got%20from%20the%20community%2C%20not%20anticipating%20that%20he'd%20eventually%20receive%201%2C167.%20He%20bailed%20after%20level%2010.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20high%20school%2C%20Agarwal%20made%20a%20single%20mobile%20app%2C%20a%20game%20called%20Toast%20Man%2C%20before%20pivoting%20back%20to%20the%20web.%20He%20set%20up%20shop%20with%20a%20site%20called%20Kamogo%2C%20where%20he%20hosted%20projects%20with%20the%20same%20inventiveness%20and%20absurdist%20energy%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20less%20polish%2C%20and%20often%20not%20much%20of%20a%20point%20%E2%80%94%20that%20would%20later%20animate%20neal.fun.%20Much%20of%20it%20still%20holds%20up.%20There's%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kamogo.com%2F5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%20Idea%20Generator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20tool%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kamogo.com%2F30%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20vertical%20videos%20horizontal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kamogo.com%2F13%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EText%20to%20Hodor%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20translator%20that%20turns%20whatever%20you%20type%20into%2C%20well%2C%20%26quot%3Bhodor.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20value%20to%20having%20somewhere%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20something%20that%20says%2C%20'This%20was%20important%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%20This%20existed.%20It%20mattered.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Agarwal%20got%20his%20first%20glimpse%20of%20mainstream%20success%20when%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-money-apple-makes-every-second-2016-8%5C%22%3Ewrote%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feverysecond.io%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeverysecond.io%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20early%20data%20visualization.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20until%20he%20was%20enrolled%20at%20Virginia%20Tech%20that%20Agarwal%20committed%20himself%20more%20fully%20to%20making%20his%20so-called%20web%20toys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProgramming%20for%20me%20was%20always%20a%20creative%20expression%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20creative%20writing.%20I%20program%20because%20I%20want%20to%20have%20the%20ideas%20in%20my%20head%20become%20a%20reality.%26quot%3B%20Formal%20computer-science%20studies%20felt%20like%20the%20exact%20opposite.%20When%20professors%20required%20students%20to%20use%20certain%20programming%20languages%2C%20Agarwal%20would%20often%20go%20his%20own%20way%20regardless%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20failing%20a%20few%20assignments%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20abject%20boredom%20Agarwal%20felt%20during%20lectures%20had%20a%20silver%20lining%3A%20the%20creation%20of%20neal.fun%2C%20which%20he%20worked%20on%20while%20he%20should%20have%20been%20taking%20notes.%20One%20of%20his%20first%20entries%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneal.fun%2Fspend%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpend%20Bill%20Gates'%20Money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20remains%20his%20most%20popular%2C%20with%20over%2080%20million%20page%20views%20since%20it%20launched%20in%202017.%20It%20took%20three%20days%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20he%20graduated%2C%20Agarwal%20was%20making%20something%20like%20a%20full-time%20living%20off%20ads%20on%20neal.fun.%20He%20gave%20himself%20a%20year%20to%20see%20if%20it%20could%20actually%20become%20a%20career.%20Two%20breakout%20visualizations%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneal.fun%2Fdeep-sea%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Deep%20Sea%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneal.fun%2Fsize-of-space%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Size%20of%20Space%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20suggested%20that%20it%20could%2C%20largely%20because%20he%20licensed%20the%20former%20to%20Ripley's%20Aquarium.%20After%20a%20detour%20working%20at%20MSCHF%2C%20a%20collective%20known%20for%20large-scale%20pranks%20and%20subversive%20art%20projects%2C%20Agarwal%20decided%20to%20go%20it%20alone%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20is%20very%2C%20very%20impressive%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Josh%20Wardle%2C%20the%20creator%20of%20Wordle%20(which%20he%20sold%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-times-buys-wordle-online-word-game-2022-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520New%2520York%2520Times%2520has%2520purchased%2520the%2520hit%2520online%2520word%2Cin%2520the%2520low%2520seven%2520figures.%2522%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20%241%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year)%2C%20and%20who%20overlapped%20with%20Agarwal%20at%20MSCHF.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20joy%20to%20his%20work%2C%20and%20a%20levity%2C%20which%20I%20think%20reflects%20how%20Neal%20sees%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVirality%20has%20seemingly%20come%20easy%20in%20the%20years%20since%2C%20including%20most%20recently%20with%20Password%20Game%2C%20which%20has%20amassed%20over%2010%20million%20page%20views%20since%20it%20launched%20in%20June.%20It's%20wholly%20original%20but%20also%20quintessentially%20neal.fun%2C%20taking%20a%20mundane%20part%20of%20internet%20life%20%E2%80%94%20password%20policies%20%E2%80%94%20to%20an%20inconceivable%20extreme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20creative%20process%20varies%20from%20project%20to%20project.%20Password%20Game%20started%20as%20a%20germ%20of%20an%20idea%20five%20years%20ago%20but%20took%20a%20few%20weeks%20to%20build%20once%20he%20got%20going.%20Internet%20Artifacts%20has%20taken%20closer%20to%20three%20months.%20He%20does%20his%20own%20research%20but%20has%20been%20increasingly%20open%20to%20soliciting%20outside%20feedback%20before%20going%20live%3B%20he%20estimates%2020%20people%20have%20given%20input%20on%20his%20internet%20museum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EInternet%20Artifacts%20takes%20several%20touchstones%20of%20the%20anteplatformian%20internet%20and%20places%20them%20on%20literal%20digital%20pedestals.%20Homestar%20Runner%20makes%20the%20cut%2C%20as%20does%20Zombo%2C%20a%20joke%20web%20page%20that%20was%20once%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fmedia%2F2003%2Fjan%2F20%2Fmondaymediasection8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanointed%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bthe%20least%20useful%20website.%26quot%3B%20Agarwal%20has%20lovingly%20recreated%20his%20references%2C%20down%20to%20a%20faithfully%20emulated%20Internet%20Explorer%20browser%20window%20for%20entries%20on%20the%20original%20MySpace%20and%20Wikipedia%20pages%2C%20and%20a%20Napster%20simulation%20that%20lets%20you%20download%20real%20MP3s.%20The%20exhibit%20unfolds%20chronologically%2C%20starting%20with%20a%201977%20map%20of%20ARPANET%2C%20the%20government-funded%20precursor%20to%20the%20modern%20internet%2C%20and%20making%20dozens%20of%20stops%20across%20the%20next%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThink%20of%20neal.fun%20as%20a%20splintered%20reality%2C%20an%20alternate%20dimension%20where%20the%20web%20never%20stopped%20being%20weird.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20surprising%20thing%20about%20Agarwal's%20undertaking%20may%20be%20that%20there's%20nothing%20really%20like%20it%20out%20there.%20(The%20closest%20thing%20may%20be%20Brandon%20Chilcutt's%20indispensable%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fsavethesounds.info%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMuseum%20of%20Endangered%20Sounds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20aural%20artifacts%20both%20on%20and%20offline%3A%20the%20whirring%20clicks%20of%20a%20rotary%20phone%2C%20a%20Tamagotchi's%20plaintive%20bloops.)%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20value%20to%20having%20somewhere%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20something%20that%20says%2C%20'This%20was%20important%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%20This%20existed.%20It%20mattered%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Jessa%20Lingel%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Gentrification%20of%20the%20Internet%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Annenberg%20School%20for%20Communication.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20shouldn't%20just%20be%20internet%20studies%20scholars%20who%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20delightful%20as%20Internet%20Artifacts%20is%20to%20click%20through%2C%20it%20also%20provides%20valuable%20context%20for%20Agarwal's%20larger%20ambition.%20Think%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fneal.fun%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneal.fun%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20splintered%20reality%2C%20an%20alternate%20dimension%20where%20the%20web%20never%20stopped%20being%20weird.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgarwal%20is%20hardly%20the%20only%20person%20making%20fun%20things%20online.%20He%20meets%20regularly%20with%20a%20group%20of%20six%20kindred%20spirits%20in%20New%20York%20to%20compare%20notes%20and%20test%20out%20ideas.%20You%20can%20find%20complementary%20energy%20in%20the%20work%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnicole.pizza%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENicole%20He%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmatthewrayfield.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMatthew%20Rayfield%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrianmoore.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrian%20Moore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.immaculategrid.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EImmaculate%20Grid%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fgames%2Fwordle%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWordle%3C%2Fa%3E%20(along%20with%20its%20infinite%20imitators)%20provide%20a%20daily%20fix%20outside%20the%20confines%20of%20the%20major%20platforms.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheuselessweb.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Useless%20Web%3C%2Fa%3E%20curates%20a%20dazzling%20selection%20of%20silliness.%20Even%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fchannel%2FUCMkbjxvwur30YrFWw8kpSaw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHomestar%20Runner%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20mounted%20a%20comeback%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20occasional%20YouTube%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20the%20variety%20of%20Agarwal's%20work%2C%20and%20his%20dedication%20to%20the%20web%20as%20a%20medium%20for%20artistic%20expression%2C%20that%20stands%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20internet%20develops%2C%20there's%20a%20bunch%20of%20things%20that%20tech%20companies%20want%20to%20do%20around%20apps%20and%20push%20notifications.%20Neal%20had%20this%20focus%20on%20not%20doing%20any%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Wardle%20said%20of%20their%20time%20as%20coworkers.%20%26quot%3BIt%20made%20me%20excited%20about%20the%20web.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20what's%20next%2C%20Agarwal%20has%20maintained%20a%20list%20of%20potential%20experiments%2C%20sorted%20by%20a%20five-star%20rating%20system%20that%20helps%20him%20prioritize%20his%20road%20map%2C%20since%20he%20was%2018.%20The%20list%20now%20numbers%20somewhere%20around%201%2C300.%20He%20still%20adds%20one%20or%20two%20each%20day.%C2%A0%20%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%2C%20even%20if%20I%20don't%20think%20of%20any%20more%20ideas%2C%20I%20have%20enough%20things%20to%20work%20on%20probably%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInternet%20Artifacts%20goes%20up%20to%202007.%20The%20last%20entry%20is%20a%20video%20of%20Steve%20Jobs%20announcing%20the%20iPhone%20at%20that%20year's%20MacWorld%20conference%2C%20played%20in%20an%20emulated%20QuickTime%20window.%20It's%20a%20fitting%20capstone%20for%20a%20certain%20era%20of%20the%20web%2C%20one%20that%20was%20open%20and%20weird%20and%20absurd.%20You're%20left%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20nostalgia%2C%20but%20also%20loss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20probably%20no%20going%20back%20to%20the%20web%20that%20was.%20Apps%20and%20platforms%20have%20fragmented%20but%20still%20dominate%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20lure%20this%20generation%20of%20creatives%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20monetization.%20But%20Agarwal's%20work%20suggests%20if%20not%20a%20return%20to%20the%20old%20ways%20then%20at%20least%20an%20alternate%20path%20forward.%20The%20web%20can%20be%20fun.%20It%20can%20be%20silly.%20It%20can%20be%20joyful.%20It%20can%20be%20anything%20you%20want.%20And%20isn't%20that%20the%20point%3F%20An%20infinite%20canvas%2C%20forever%20in%20search%20of%20an%20artist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBrian%20Barrett%20is%20the%20former%20executive%20editor%20of%20Wired%C2%A0and%20author%20of%20The%20Art%20of%20the%20Minifigure.%20He%20has%20also%20written%20for%20The%20New%20Yorker%2C%20The%20Atlantic%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20numerous%20other%20publications.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneal-agarwal-saves-internet-making-web-fun-again-games-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%