al%2Futtarakhand-4-months-3-chief-ministers-1004928.html%5C%22%3Ethree%20CMs%20in%20four%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20mid-2021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20healthy%20trend%20in%20the%20Congress%20has%20been%20the%20grooming%20of%20a%20leadership%20structure%20in%20states.%20The%20new%20policy%20is%20based%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20elections%20are%20won%20on%20cooperative%20efforts%20by%20the%20central%20and%20state%20leaders.%20This%20is%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20policy%20of%20treating%20state%20leaders%20as%20dispensable%20and%20seeking%20votes%20by%20leveraging%20his%20popularity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20all%20good%20authoritarian%20leaders%2C%20his%20emphasis%20has%20been%20to%20directly%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20voters%20without%20anyone%20in%20between.%20This%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Fgujarat-new-cabinet-delayed-as-old-guard-weighs-on-fresh-start%2Farticleshow%2F86249775.cms%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20revolts%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20leaders%20who%20had%20devoted%20their%20entire%20lives%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20were%20ignored.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdouble-engine-bjp-modi-shah%5C%22%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Double%20Engine%E2%80%99%20is%20Pass%C3%A9%2C%20Hereafter%20Modi-Shah%20Will%20Pick%20or%20Junk%20BJP%20CMs%20at%20Will%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20dissent%20to%20consensus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%20suffered%20its%20worst%20desertions%20after%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20when%20its%20tally%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20just%2052.%20Narendra%20Modi%20emerged%20as%20an%20uncrowned%20king.%20The%20party%20had%20to%20contend%20with%20large-scale%20defections%2C%20some%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20others%20to%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress.%20Incidentally%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20been%20very%20selective%20in%20accommodating%20defectors%20from%20the%20Congress.%20Those%20were%20the%20days%20when%20the%20Congress%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Flike-a-drowning-boat-in-turbulent-ocean-g23-leaders-on-congress-debacle-1090599.html%5C%22%3Esinking%20boat%20in%20a%20turbulent%20sea%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20a%20group%20of%2023%20senior%20leaders%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20interim%20Congress%20president%20Indira%20Gandhi%20demanded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fgroup-of-23-the-congress-leaders-who-wrote-the-letter-of-dissent-why-they-are-important-2813123.html%5C%22%3Ewide-ranging%20reforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20included%20collective%20leadership%20and%20elections%20to%20choose%20the%20party%20president%20and%20all%20organisational%20committees.%20Among%20this%20%E2%80%98G-23%E2%80%99%20were%20senior%20leaders%20like%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20Anand%20Sharma%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%20and%20Manish%20Tiwari%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20phenomenon%20lasted%20for%20about%20two%20years%20while%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20remained%20adamant.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20many%20more%20members%20departed.%20Some%20like%20Jitin%20Prasada%20joined%20the%20BJP%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%20became%20an%20independent%20leader%20and%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%20formed%20his%20own%20party.%20Initially%2C%20the%20leadership%20dismissed%20the%20G-23%20implosion%20as%20a%20revolt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20G-23%20also%20eventually%20triggered%20the%20transformation%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20as%20a%20vigorous%20movement.%20The%20process%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20had%20begun%20even%20before%20Kharge%E2%80%99s%20election%20as%20president%20and%20the%20appointment%20of%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20as%20AICC%E2%80%99s%20communication%20head.%20The%20G-23%20is%20now%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past.%20Most%20of%20its%20prominent%20members%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-working-committee-reshuffle-shashi-tharoor-sachin-pilot-and-gaurav-gogoi-among-20-new-faces-inducted-101692556638462.html%5C%22%3Eaccommodated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20or%20other%20important%20positions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202022%2C%20regional%20parties%20like%20TMC%20and%20KCR%E2%80%99s%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20had%20opened%20offices%20in%20Delhi.%20This%20was%20part%20of%20their%20prime%20ministerial%20ambitions.%20The%20Congress%20resurgence%20has%20made%20them%20retreat.%20Among%20the%20opposition%20parties%2C%20the%20Congress%20alone%20has%20the%20infrastructure%20to%20daily%20pound%20the%20ruling%20party%20on%20emerging%20issues%2C%20including%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Gautam%20Adani.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20list%20is%20finalised%20by%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20his%20technocrats%2C%20the%20Congress%20this%20time%20is%20experimenting%20with%20a%20new%20system%20to%20provide%20more%20power%20to%20state%20leaders.%20The%20selection%20of%20candidates%20was%20left%20to%20the%20state%20leaders.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20central%20election%20committee%20focused%20on%20trying%20for%20consensus%20on%20disputed%20names.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20new%20system%20has%20worked%20smoothly.%20There%20were%20a%20few%20protests%20by%20the%20disappointed%20aspirants%2C%20which%20is%20to%20be%20expected.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F11191048%2Fcongress-leaders.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F11191048%2Fcongress-leaders.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F11191048%2Fcongress-leaders-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F11191048%2Fcongress-leaders-1024x511.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F11191048%2Fcongress-leaders-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-419904%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EP.%20Chidambaram%2C%20Anand%20Sharma%20and%20Kapil%20Sibal%20were%20among%20the%20G-23%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGhar%20wapsi%20of%20leaders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProof%20of%20the%20Congress%20resurgence%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20frantic%20%3Cem%3Eghar%20wapsi%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20the%20party%20during%20the%20past%20six%20months.%20And%20this%20massive%20exodus%20happened%20without%20the%20support%20of%20raids%20by%20investigating%20agencies.%20Here%20is%20a%20partial%20list%20of%20those%20who%20joined%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EKasireddy%20Narayan%20Reddy%2C%20BRS%20MLC%2C%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20October%206.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EL.B.%20Nagar%20BRS%20leader%20Rammohan%20Goud%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20October%2012.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EBRS%20leaders%20Mynampally%20Hanumanth%20Rao%20and%20Vemula%20Veeresham%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20September%2029.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20BRS%20leader%20Tummala%20Nageswara%20Rao%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20September%2016.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EThirty-five%20BRS%20leaders%2C%20including%20former%20MP%20Ponguleti%20Srinivas%20Reddy%20and%20ex-minister%20Jupally%20Krishna%20Rao%2C%20joined%20the%20Congress%20in%20late%20June.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20several%20MLAs%20from%20the%20Gwalior-Chambal%20region%20who%20left%20the%20Congress%20along%20with%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%20have%20rejoined%20the%20party.%20These%20include%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EVirendra%20Raghuvanshi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Promod%20Tandon%2C%20Ramkishore%20Shula%20and%20Dinesh%20Mallar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EOBC%20leader%20and%20former%20MP%20Bodh%20Singh%20Bhagat%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20September%2021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20former%20two-term%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20BJP%20MLA%2C%20Girija%20Shankar%2C%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20September%2011.%20Eight%20days%20earlier%2C%2010%20BJP%20leaders%2C%20including%20an%20MLA%20and%20a%20former%20legislator%2C%20switched%20to%20the%20Congress.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3ERajesh%20Patel%2C%20a%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20in%20the%20Budhni%20assembly%20segment%2C%20joined%20the%20Congress%20on%20September%2021.%20His%20father%20was%20a%20Jan%20Sangh%20leader.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20October%2016%2C%20several%20BJP%20and%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20leaders%20in%20Punjab%20joined%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20October%2019%2C%20several%20BJP%20and%20AAP%20leaders%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20including%20an%20ex-MLA%2C%20joined%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttempts%20to%20counter%20%E2%80%98anti-Hindu%E2%80%99%20allegations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20arrogance%20with%20which%20the%20BJP%20pushes%20its%20hard%20Hindutva%20has%20reverberations%20in%20other%20parties.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Congress%20is%20often%20targeted%20with%20allegations%20of%20%E2%80%98minority%20appeasement%E2%80%99%20and%20being%20%E2%80%98anti-Hindu%E2%80%99.%20