20allowed%20%E2%80%9Cbeing%20there%20for%E2%80%9D%20the%20animal%2C%20and%20what%20that%20could%20mean.%20These%20are%20the%20onion%20layers%20within%20which%20the%20activists%2Finterlocutors%20she%20focuses%20on%20move.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20herself%20has%20volunteered%20at%20a%20number%20of%20the%20sites%20that%20she%20describes%2C%20which%20deepens%20her%20observational%20span.%20She%20takes%20gestures%2C%20phrases%2C%20moods%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20look%20in%20the%20animal%E2%80%99s%20eye%20as%20the%20material%20for%20her%20reflections%2C%20keeping%20the%20book%20both%20wonderfully%20imaginative%20and%20honest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EInjury%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20takes%20off%20from%20the%20injury%20to%20the%20animal.%20The%20early%20part%20of%20the%20book%20focuses%20on%20the%20animal%20rights%20warriors%20who%20have%20set%20up%20NGOs%20and%20shelters%20across%20the%20country%20over%20the%20past%20century.%20These%20have%20been%20successful%20in%20passing%20legislation%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Cruelty%20to%20Animals%20Act%2C%201960%2C%20which%20frames%20much%20of%20urban%20legal%20work%20today.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20uses%20her%20ethnography%20at%20their%20offices%20and%20shelters%20to%20offer%20insights%20on%20their%20historical%20location%2C%20their%20motivations%2C%20and%20especially%20their%20relationships%20to%20the%20fascism%20of%20the%20mid-20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%2C%20given%20fascism%E2%80%99s%20own%20troubled%20relationship%20to%20nature%20and%20animals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20observes%20how%20the%20highest%20caste%20of%20animal%20lovers%20%E2%80%93%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20parliamentarian%20Menaka%20Gandhi%2C%20and%20the%20upper%20class%20women%20animal%20lovers%20(Savitri%20Devi%2C%20Rukmini%20Devi%2C%20Crystal%20Rogers)%20thought%2C%20talked%2C%20legislated%2C%20and%20took%20deep%20care%20of%20abandoned%20and%20other%20animals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20tracks%20their%20%E2%80%9Ccompassion%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20%E2%80%9Caffective%20history%20of%20liberalism%E2%80%9D.%20It%20notes%20that%20all%20three%20women%20were%20childless%2C%20and%20extends%20this%20into%20a%20study%20of%20their%20%E2%80%9Cconversion%E2%80%9D%20into%20animal%20lovers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20also%20travels%20with%20the%20class-regular%2C%20male%2C%20animal%20medical%20caregivers%20in%20the%20trains%20and%20streets%20of%20Bombay%2C%20to%20observe%20how%20the%20carers%20pick%2C%20hold%2C%20heal%20and%20touch%20wounded%20animals%2C%20put%20them%20back%20on%20the%20street%2C%20and%20return%20again%20and%20again%20to%20take%20care%20of%20them%2C%20the%20futility%20of%20it%20all%20notwithstanding.%20The%20author%20notices%20how%20these%20carers%20navigate%20within%20the%20inevitable%20ethical%20contradictions%20they%20encounter%20without%20avoiding%20or%20rising%20above%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F28170623%2FScreenshot-2022-05-28-at-5.06.02-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22771%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F28170623%2FScreenshot-2022-05-28-at-5.06.02-PM.png%20771w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F28170623%2FScreenshot-2022-05-28-at-5.06.02-PM-300x202.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-598771%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22519%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20human-animal%20relationship.%20Photo%3A%20Jignesh%20Mistry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20visits%20farms%20and%20shelters%20made%20for%20abandoned%20animals%2C%20butcher%20shops%20and%20slaughterhouses%2C%20with%20equally%20fascinating%20descriptions%20and%20reflections%20on%20contradictions%20like%20a%20millionaire%20Jain%20egg%20seller.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reader%20gets%20a%20glimpse%20into%20these%20disparate%20worlds%2C%20each%20of%20which%20is%20carefully%20shot%20through%20with%20literary%2C%20mythological%2C%20historical%2C%20and%20philosophical%20digressions%20used%20for%20her%20ethical%20exploration.%20On%20a%20different%20register%2C%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20stories%20serve%20to%20document%20%E2%80%9Cexperiments%20in%20truth%E2%80%9D%20by%20a%20range%20of%20actors%20across%20urban%20and%20peri-urban%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndifference%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20track%20on%20which%20the%20book%20runs%20is%20its%20advocacy%20for%20an%20ethics%20of%20%E2%80%9Cindifference%E2%80%9D.%20We%20are%20asked%20to%20think%20about%20positioning%20ourselves%20not%20on%20the%20side%20of%2C%20but%2C%20as%20side%20to%20side%20with%2C%20that%20which%20we%20care%20about.%20This%20brings%20sharply%20to%20mind%20the%20recently%20much-circulated%20article%20by%20Arielle%20Angel%2C%20editor%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJewish%20Currents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20on%20how%20Left%20Israeli-Palestinian%20relationships%20have%20broken%20down%20in%20this%20current%20moment%20for%20insufficiently%20being%20on%20the%20side%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ewith%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cindifference%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20author%20cites%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccultivated%20demeanour%2C%20that%20is%20born%20of%20the%20queer%20desire%20and%20the%20queer%20belief%20in%20an%20otherwise%20way%20of%20being%E2%80%9D.%20This%20being%20quite%20insufficient%2C%20I%20went%20on%20to%20read%20one%20of%20the%20other%20citations%20she%20provides%20%E2%80%93%20Fran%20Tonkiss%2C%20on%20indifference%20in%20the%20western%20city.%20Tonkiss%20explores%20indifference%20in%20relation%20to%20anonymity%2C%20a%20capacity%20to%20be%20unseen%2C%20and%20the%20claim%20to%20solitude.%20She%20takes%20the%20example%20of%20women%20for%20whom%20invisibility%20in%20the%20public%20sphere%20is%20frequently%20welcomed%2C%20and%20that%20it%20can%20be%20the%20basis%20of%20positive%20claims%20or%20rights.%20Indifference%20militates%20against%20the%20ethic%20of%20tight%20community%20which%20invariably%20turns%20insular.%20Whereas%20difference%20requires%20recognition%2C%20indifference%20requires%20respect.%20It%20is%20an%20alternative%20mode%20of%20political%20engagement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fhumans-animals-photo-story%5C%22%3E%20In%20Photos%3A%20The%20Symbiotic%20Relationship%20Between%20Humans%20and%20Animals%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20author%20then%20takes%20this%20notion%20of%20indifference%20and%20explores%20its%20value%20in%20relation%20to%20human-animal%20relations%20in%20the%20Indian%20context.%20The%20reader%20is%20taken%20on%20a%20journey%20through%20a%20series%20of%20alliterative%20reflections%20by%20theorists%20of%20animals%2Fhumans%20to%20draw%20out%20aspects%20of%20this%20ethic.%20This%20is%20a%20generative%20intellectual%20process%20(though%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20reader).%20It%20does%20not%20fill%20us%20with%20facts%2F%20knowledge%20or%20too%20much%20context.%20Rather%2C%20it%20suggests%20some%20lessons.%20For%20one%2C%20animals%20need%20not%20be%20the%20%E2%80%9Cobject%E2%80%9D%20of%20our%20attention%2C%20but%20exist%20as%20fellow%20beings.%20The%20idea%20of%20the%20ethic%20of%20indifference%20really%20comes%20to%20life%20when%20we%20travel%20with%20the%20caregivers%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Bombay%20tending%20to%20injured%20animals%2C%20that%20are%20both%20familiar%20to%20them%2C%20but%20who%20are%20also%20given%20complete%20autonomy.%20They%20do%20not%20seek%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%E2%80%9D%20them%2C%20in%20glaring%20contrast%20to%20the%20rubric%20of%20the%20Animal%20Protection%20Act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20also%20takes%20a%20good%20stab%20at%20%E2%80%9Ccuriosity%E2%80%9D.%20This%20of%20course%20is%20a%20notorious%20element%20of%20Indian%20middle-class%20behaviour%2C%20standing%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20intelligence%2C%20a%20harbinger%20of%20success%2C%20as%20well%20as%20for%20the%20inevitable%20policing.%20The%20author%20rather%20suggests%20that%20the%20curious%20gaze%20(metonymic%20to%20ingesting%2C%20consuming%2C%20appropriating%20stealing%2C%20exhibiting%2C%20mastery%2C%20etc.)%20should%20give%20way%20to%20appreciating%20%E2%80%9Copacity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20thought%20she%20was%20being%20unnecessarily%20contrary%20here%2C%20but%20she%20defends%20it%20stoutly%20as%20a%20refusal%20to%20be%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20knower%20or%20the%20known%20(human%20and%20animal)%2C%20a%20deliberate%20refusal%2C%20so%20as%20to%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ebe%20on%20the%20side%20of%20freedom%2C%20against%20predation%2C%20and%20to%20be%20respectful%20of%20singular%20opacities.%20We%20cannot%20after%20all%20ever%20know%20what%20an%20animal%20knows%20or%20sees%20as%20the%20animal%20sees.%20So%2C%20again%2C%20indifference%2C%20not%20curiosity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20moves%20her%20into%20advocating%20for%20the%20mutual%20regard%20of%20opaque%20differences%20over%20the%20desire%20or%20will%20to%20%E2%80%9Cgrasp%E2%80%9D%20differences.%20In%20passing%2C%20she%20sideswipes%20love%2C%20and%20animus%2C%20both%20being%20as%20exploitative%20as%20curiosity.%20These%20are%20also%20the%20main%20emotional%20valences%20that%20come%20up%20through%20some%20of%20her%20earlier%20human%20interlocutors%20(the%20animal%20lovers).%20Rather%2C%20it%20is%20care%2C%20and%20not%20the%20passions%20of%20love%20or%20hate%2C%20that%20drives%20the%20ethic%20of%20indifference.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-extract-a-dogs-tale-of-gossip-myth-and-mischief%5C%22%3EBook%20Extract%3A%20A%20Dog%E2%80%99s%20Tale%20of%20Gossip%2C%20Myth%20and%20Mischief%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnimals%20are%20frequently%20posited%20as%20the%20truer%20ethical%20actors%20in%20this%20book%3A%20they%20refuse%2C%20they%20are%20indifferent%2C%20they%20are%20never%20violently%20curious.%20She%20does%20not%20say%20if%20her%20ethic%20of%20indifference%20emerges%20from%20how%20animals%20actually%20%E2%80%9Care%E2%80%9D.%20Yet%2C%20that%20is%20how%20I%20choose%20to%20read%20it%2C%20though%20this%20can%20also%20only%20be%20a%20gross%20generalisation%20on%20my%20part.%20I%20also%20think%20she%20reads%20in%20bourgeois%20or%20captive%20individualism%20to%20animals%E2%80%99%20life-worlds.%20The%20absence%20of%20predators%20(eg.%20big%20cats)%20as%20her%20focus%20possibly%20allows%20this.%20What%20she%20convincingly%20suggests%2C%20however%2C%20is%20how%20the%20interspecies%20interface%20is%20very%20fuzzy%20and%20neither%20animal%20nor%20human.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlternately%2C%20from%20a%20naturalist%E2%80%99s%20lens%2C%20this%20interface%20contains%20interconnections%20and%20webs%2C%20including%20dependencies%2C%20and%20much%20else.%20The%20author%20does%20not%20explore%20this%2C%20which%20would%20have%20added%20a%20rich%20dimension%20to%20her%20study.%20For%20instance%2C%20as%20she%20asks%2C%20why%20do%20the%20most%20committed%20upper-caste%20activists%20feel%20that%20they%20want%20to%20hear%20the%20very%20screams%20of%20the%20animal.%20They%20want%20that%20pain%2C%20she%20suggests%2C%20so%20as%20to%20shed%20their%20skins%2C%20and%20be%20re-born.%20But%20what%20else%20is%20this%20absorption%2C%20mimicry%2C%20and%20moulting%2C%20about%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%2C%20through%20all%20that%20it%20records%2C%20has%20many%20moments%20where%20the%20reader%20simply%20stops%20in%20wonder%2C%20for%20we%20see%20the%20author%20has%20identified%20yet%20another%20ethical%20knot%2C%20and%20is%20attempting%20to%20unravel%20it.%20I%20have%20only%20mentioned%20a%20few%20of%20the%20areas%20she%20traverses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20slight%20book%2C%20and%20not%20a%20manifesto%2C%20but%20with%20its%20heart%20firmly%20located%20in%20animal-human%20relations.%20Maybe%20the%20best%20praise%20of%20it%20is%20to%20say%20that%20the%20book%20offers%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98how%20we%20go%20from%20here%20to%20there%E2%80%99%20within%20the%20horrific%20context%20of%20our%20world.%20Its%20ethic%20of%20indifference%20is%20an%20ethic%20of%20survival%2C%20to%20be%20along-side%20the%20neighbour%2C%20who%20may%20not%20look%2C%20sound%2C%20behave%2C%20feel%20like%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQueer%20listening%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20track%20in%20the%20book%20is%20autobiographical.%20The%20details%20she%20provides%20on%20her%20childhood%20and%20certain%20formative%20moments%20is%20a%20gesture%20to%20transparency%2C%20despite%20the%20call%20for%20opacity.%20It%20humorously%20explains%20personal%20choices%2C%20for%20instance%20veganism%2C%20while%20acknowledging%20the%20politics%20of%20beef-eating.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20this%20track%20helps%20in%20the%20highly%20contentious%2C%20boxed%2C%20hierarchical%20and%20normatively%20anti-queer%20world%2C%20that%20is%20India%2C%20which%20has%20made%20self-righteous%20judges%20of%20us%20all%2C%20to%20more%20properly%20place%20the%20author%20and%20her%20investments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F09%2Fcows-copy.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Slaughter%20is%20required%20to%20balance%20the%20cycle%20of%20production%2C%20disposal%20and%20replacement%20of%20domestic%20farm%20animals%20in%20farmer%20livelihoods.%20Credit%3A%20Pixabay%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-181255%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentational%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Pixabay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20her%20investments%20is%20in%20%E2%80%9Cqueer%20listening%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20a%20fascinating%20discussion.%20In%20it%2C%20she%20explores%20the%20silences%20but%20also%20the%20speech%20of%20animals%2C%20while%20cautioning%20on%20not%20ever%20representing%20them.%20She%20tells%20the%20stories%20of%20the%20hen%20that%20spoke%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20abolishment%20of%20capital%20punishment%20in%20France%2C%20of%20the%20Brigadier%20General%20who%20gave%20up%20selling%20milk%20from%20his%20cows%20after%20the%20cow%20entered%20his%20dreams!%20Such%20queer%20worlds%20offer%20seeds%20or%20sources%20for%20alternatives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECuriously%2C%20she%20does%20not%20say%20anything%20on%20the%20trend%20towards%20the%20legal%20rights%20of%20living%20beings.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20think%20she%20does%20not%20have%20much%20use%20for%20it%2C%20as%20it%20confines%20animals%20within%20human%20rules%20and%20codes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHere%2C%20we%20note%20the%20author%20evinces%20a%20commitment%20to%20something%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdepolitical%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20an%20ongoing%20refusal%20to%20be%20determined%2C%20decided%20for%2C%20enclosed%2C%20made%20useful%2C%20or%20made%20sensible%20through%20and%20for%20lines%20of%20force%E2%80%9D%20which%20raises%20for%20her%20the%20question%20of%20%E2%80%9Chow%20do%20we%20nurture%20a%20politics%20that%20is%20not%20sterile%2C%20that%20is%20not%20all%20cramped%20up%20with%20concerns%20about%20structure%2C%20boundaries%2C%20and%20the%20proper%20relationship%20between%20concepts%E2%80%9D.%20She%20suggests%20nomadic%20creativity%20of%20inventing%20queer%20frames.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20some%20of%20this%20is%20evident%20in%20the%20stories%20she%20tells%2C%20the%20author%20does%20not%20really%20explain%20what%20she%20means.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20also%20many%20other%20areas%20of%20ethics%20in%20the%20burgeoning%20field%20of%20animal-human%20relations%2C%20where%20this%20book%20does%20not%20go.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20extreme%20digital%20tech%20that%20has%20invaded%20the%20animal-human%20world%2C%20as%20noticed%20in%20Nayanika%20Mathur%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECrooked%20Cats%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Does%20the%20author%20agree%20with%20Mathur%20that%20the%20compassion%20that%20animals%20evoke%20is%20not%20transferable%20to%20human%20subjects%2C%20that%20human-animal%20conflict%20has%20increased%20with%20the%20successes%20in%20conservation%2C%20etc.%20But%20she%20does%20not%20make%20this%20a%20comparative%20conversation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20this%20book%20adds%20to%20the%20faith%20one%20can%20have%20in%20this%20new%20generation%20of%20scholars%20who%2C%20through%20their%20close%20investment%20in%20the%20animal%20and%20natural%20world%2C%20are%20charting%20fabulous%20new%20areas%20of%20knowledge%2C%20wisdom%20and%20ethics.%20This%20has%20not%20been%20the%20case%20for%20a%20long%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20get%20back%20to%20the%20autobiographical%20track%2C%20the%20author%20notices%20that%20most%20scholars%20and%20artists%20write%20to%20live%20with%20ourselves%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20to%20reconcile%20but%20to%20voice%20our%20hauntings%20and%20make%20of%20them%20an%20inheritance%20that%20cares%20for%20the%20survival%20and%20thriving%20of%20those%20who%20live%20under%20relations%20of%20conquest%20in%20which%20we%20too%20are%20embedded%2C%20complicit%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20so%20many%20ways%2C%20then%2C%20the%20book%20is%20a%20valuable%20document%20of%20record%2C%20history%20and%20storytelling.%20It%20is%20a%20call%20for%20ethical%20reflection%20to%20guide%20action%20towards%20caring.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ESara%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Abraham%20is%20a%20lawyer%20based%20in%20Chennai.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698301253000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F10152507%2FScreenshot-2022-08-10-at-3.24.16-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhumans-animals-and-a-millionaire-egg-seller%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Naisargi%20Dave%E2%80%99s%20illuminating%20book%20'Indifference%3A%20On%20the%20Praxis%20of%20Interspecies%20Being'%20offers%20an%20interesting%20perspective%20on%20the%20fraught%20relations%20between%20humans%20and%20animals%20in%20urban%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhumans-animals-and-a-millionaire-egg-seller%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%3A%20Multiple%20People%20Killed%20in%20Mass%20Shootings%20in%20Maine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F02163509%2Fdavid-von-diemar-jM6Y2nhsAtk-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funited-states-of-america%2Ft-19065189%5C%22%3EUS%3C%2Fa%3E%20city%20of%20Lewiston%20in%20Maine%20on%20Wednesday%20launched%20a%20manhunt%20for%20a%20suspect%C2%A0who%20opened%20fire%20on%20a%20bar%20and%20a%20bowling%20alley.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPolice%20have%20yet%20to%20confirm%20the%20number%20of%20people%20killed%20and%20i