21%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20than%2011%2C000%20Indians%20also%20received%20a%20passport%20of%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20in%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchart-us-australia-canada-added-100000-new-citizens-from-india-in-2021%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Civil%20Servants'%20Authority%20Will%20Be%20Weakened%20if%20They%20Are%20Used%20for%20Poll%20Campaigning%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26083156%2FFu9XIQ-XwAAdeEH.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Constitution%20was%20being%20framed%2C%20there%20were%20concerns%20about%20the%20civil%20services.%20India%E2%80%99s%20home%20minister%20Sardar%20Patel%20had%20famously%20observed%20that%20he%20had%20asked%20his%20secretary%20to%20give%20his%20views%20freely.%20He%20had%20no%20use%20for%20civil%20servants%20who%20wanted%20to%20echo%20the%20views%20of%20the%20political%20masters.%20He%20wanted%20their%20independent%20opinion%20on%20issues%2C%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20governance.%20The%20civil%20services%20were%20thus%20expected%20to%20be%20apolitical.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201970s%20there%20were%20efforts%20to%20dilute%20this%20approach.%20There%20was%20talk%20of%20a%20committed%20civil%20service.%20Questions%20were%20asked%20%E2%80%95%20committed%20to%20whom%3F%20The%20civil%20service%20could%20only%20be%20committed%20to%20the%20Constitution.%20It%20could%20not%20have%20commitments%20in%20favour%20of%20any%20politician%2C%20party%20or%20ideology.%20It%20had%20to%20implement%20policies%20of%20the%20government%20in%20power.%20But%20it%20could%20not%20be%20committed%20to%20their%20political%20ideology%2C%20good%20or%20bad.%20Their%20responsibility%20was%20to%20help%20frame%20policies%20for%20welfare%20and%20economic%20growth%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20ministers%20or%20the%20cabinet.%20They%20were%20expected%20to%20implement%20these%20effectively%20and%20ensure%20that%20people%20got%20the%20full%20benefit%20of%20these%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20achievements%20of%20any%20government%20are%20projected%20through%20the%20media%2C%20for%20which%20the%20publicity%20wings%20of%20the%20government%20are%20specifically%20responsible.%20Political%20masters%20talk%20about%20these%20achievements%20in%20their%20speeches.%20They%20tell%20the%20people%20how%20much%20good%20work%20they%20are%20doing.%20The%20civil%20servants%20only%20explain%20to%20the%20common%20man%20the%20intricacies%20of%20policies%20and%20how%20they%20can%20use%20any%20scheme%20for%20their%20welfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20recent%20media%20reports%20indicate%20that%20a%20large%20body%20of%20civil%20servants%20would%20be%20expected%20to%20tell%20the%20people%20about%20the%20good%20work%20of%20the%20government%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%20There%20is%20a%20campaign%20mode%20being%20prescribed%20for%20this.%20This%20is%20very%20unfortunate.%20Whether%20the%20government%20has%20done%20well%20or%20badly%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20is%20not%20for%20them%20to%20say.%20They%20can%20only%20describe%20policies%20in%20their%20sectors.%20This%20approach%20may%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20politicisation%20of%20bureaucracy%2C%20which%20is%20very%20unfortunate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20another%20aspect%20of%20this%20issue.%20Governments%20in%20different%20states%20are%20run%20by%20different%20political%20parties.%20Many%20states%20have%20their%20own%20schemes.%20During%20elections%2C%20states%20ruled%20by%20parties%20opposed%20to%20the%20Centre%20may%20like%20to%20propagate%20their%20own%20policies.%20They%20may%20like%20to%20tell%20people%20how%20badly%20the%20Centre%20is%20doing%20and%20how%20well%20they%20themselves%20are%20working.%20This%20would%20create%20problems%20in%20implementing%20the%20idea%20of%20projecting%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20issue%20involved%20here%20is%20our%20long%20term-view%20of%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20civil%20service.%20While%20the%20campaign%20planned%20may%20give%20some%20benefits%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20it%20may%20open%20the%20door%20to%20a%20civil%20service%20of%20poor%20quality.%20The%20essence%20of%20a%20democracy%20and%20good%20governance%20is%20that%20civil%20servants%20try%20to%20improve%20their%20professionalism%20in%20framing%20policies%20and%20ensuring%20maximum%20benefits%20to%20the%20people.%20They%20specialise%20in%20effectively%20implementing%20government%20policies%20to%20ensure%20maximum%20benefits%20to%20people.%20Whether%20an%20approach%20or%20programme%20is%20superior%20or%20inferior%20to%20the%20earlier%20government%E2%80%99s%20is%20not%20their%20business.%20But%20now%2C%20they%20are%20being%20effectively%20called%20upon%20to%20identify%20with%20one%20government.%20This%20is%20not%20part%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20system%20of%20governance.%20Governments%20come%20and%20go%20but%20the%20civil%20servants%20remain%20a%20neutral%20observer.%20The%20current%20orders%20of%20the%20government%20are%20completely%20in%20violation%20of%20this%20spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20on%20this%20issue%20is%20difficult%20to%20understand%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ongoing%20election%20process%2C%20during%20which%20the%20state%20machinery%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completely%20neutral.%20To%20argue%20that%20those%20representatives%20of%20the%20Centre%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20disseminate%20achievements%20of%20the%20party%20in%20power%20is%20clearly%20unfair.%20The%20Election%20Commission%20may%20take%20note%20of%20it%20and%20review%20this%20programme%20for%20poll-bound%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EB.K.%20Chaturvedi%20is%20former%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20and%20member%2C%20Planning%20Commission.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698289366000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%